review_title: All management and administration including Lance should be replaced.
job_title: in Winter Haven, FL
pros: PTO earned. I have a job.
cons: Paid time off can't be used for what it's there for. It supposed to be for sick time, which unfortunately can't be scheduled. Floors are always short staffed so you create problems when you're not there. All problems are brushed under the rug by higher ups. They are where they want to be so no one wants to do anything about real issues. They're all friends and don't care about the employees actually doing the work nor do they have any respect for them. They get big bonuses at the regular employees expense. The motto of my manager is "if you don't like it LEAVE and there is a line of people to replace you for less pay," and the pay isn't much! The scholarships that are awarded go to RNs and people in management that can afford to pay for their own further education. They go to school to be able to do even less work than they already do for more money. They should go to the $10 people who are trying to better themselves and raise their families. My boss gets a big scholarship for college and won't allow the us attend if it affects the schedule. I would not be treated at this hospital. Most of the nursing personnel are incompetent. There are some good nurses but they are spread so thin.

job_title: Registered Nurse 20+ Years Experience in Winter Haven, FL
pros: Short distance from where I live.
cons:
Staff is overrun with incompetent nurses who show a complete lack of concern for patients.  I worked with nurses who NEVER WASHED THEIR HANDS as evidenced by ink marks that remained on their hands throughout the shift & the next day.
Cardiac nurses who were unable in read an EKG.
Floor nurses who were clueless about medication administration.
Management is unconcerned with patient wellfare.
Paid time off shortchanged regularly in pay checks.
No employee discount in cafeteria, food is lousy anyway.
Nurses leaving the building while on the clock to run errands.
Nurses who sleep on the job. There is one on who sets up a chair in the bathroom so she can put up her feet & sleep in privacy, management is aware of this & does nothing.
RNs who don't access patients.
Medications marked as given when they were not.
Employees who are ALWAYS LATE.  This is never addressed by management.
Incompetent nurses are promoted, good nurses who speak up about conditions in this hospital are encouraged to leave.
I worked there for two years and was lucky to leave with an intact license. 
The thought of being a patient in this institution fills me with terror.
If you are thinking of working at Winter Haven Hospital think again. This is not a place for a caring nurse. If you are unsure about which end of the syringe to insert into the patient this is the place for you, go for it!
